    "blockingIssues": [
      {
        "id": "B1",
        "title": "Decision 1 (Semantic Colors) underestimates scope — plan says 'swap 6 CSS vars' but actual change is far larger",
        "detail": "The plan claims 'highest impact, lowest effort — swap 6 CSS vars'. In reality: (1) index.css has 3 light-mode color vars (success/warning/danger) but needs 12 new tokens (base/bg/border × 4 categories), (2) dark mode needs 12 additional overrides in the [data-theme='dark'] block, (3) the Badge component uses foreground/alpha patterns (e.g., 'bg-foreground/5 text-foreground') not color tokens — all 9 Badge variants need rewriting, (4) ~30+ places in 15+ files use text-success/text-warning/text-danger/bg-danger etc. that need updating, (5) Button variants (danger, success) reference these tokens, (6) Toast component uses semantic color classes. This is a medium-effort change spanning the entire component library, not a '6 CSS vars' swap."
      },
      {
        "id": "B2",
        "title": "No Collapsible/Accordion component exists — Decision 2 requires building one",
        "detail": "The plan assumes wrapping sections in 'collapsible containers' but the ui/ component library has no Collapsible or Accordion component. The only collapsible pattern in the codebase is ad-hoc useState-based toggling (EvidenceDrawer, WhatIfPanel, Plan History). A reusable CollapsibleSection component needs to be created first, supporting: default open/closed state, localStorage persistence of expansion state, summary/badge slot for collapsed preview, 'Expand all / Collapse all' coordination. This is a prerequisite step the plan doesn't mention."
      },
      {
        "id": "B3",
        "title": "Decision 4 (Typography) requires adding Inter font — no Inter/Geist Sans exists in the project",
        "detail": "The plan recommends Inter as the primary proportional font, but the project only loads Geist Mono via Google Fonts CDN. Neither Inter nor Geist Sans is referenced anywhere. Steps needed: (1) add Inter font import to index.css or install it as a package, (2) change --font-family-base, (3) Tailwind v4's @theme needs the new value, (4) body already uses var(--font-family-base), so the base swap propagates, BUT (5) many components (commit titles, ticket IDs, etc.) need explicit font-mono class added since they currently inherit the mono font from body. The plan doesn't list which components need explicit font-mono annotation."
      },
      {
        "id": "B4",
        "title": "Decision 5 (Charts) doesn't account for Tremor v3 → v4 API changes and Tailwind v4 compatibility",
        "detail": "The project uses Tailwind CSS v4 (@tailwindcss/vite 4.2.2) which uses the new CSS-first configuration (@theme instead of tailwind.config.js). Tremor (recommended library) historically requires tailwind.config.js and has specific plugin setup. Need to verify Tremor v3/v4 is compatible with Tailwind v4's new config system. If not, Recharts (framework-agnostic) would be the safer choice. The plan should specify the exact version and verify compatibility."
